UAMethod.Description: The SetFloorOffset method accepts shield parameters and drum height correction offsets and returns a boolean to indicate succesfull execution

uax:Description.uax:Text: The StartShield property describes the start shield position from which on the drum height correction shall be applied
The EndShield property describes the end shield position until which the drum height correction shall be applied to
The FaceOffset property describes the drum height correction
The FloorOffsetResult property describes the successfull execution of the SetFloorOffset method
